production"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EBrunner glands are located in the submucosa of the duodenum. Their primary function is to secrete \u003Cstrong\u003Ealkaline mucus\u003C/strong\u003E containing bicarbonate ions, which helps protect the duodenal mucosa from acidic chyme entering from the stomach.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThese glands do not \u003Cstrong\u003Eproduce digestive enzymes\u003C/strong\u003E, which mainly come from the pancreas.  \u003Cstrong\u003ECholecystokinin\u003C/strong\u003E stimulates gallbladder contraction and is produced by I cells in the duodenum and jejunum.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntrinsic factor\u003C/strong\u003E is produced by parietal cells in the stomach  for vitamin B12 absorption. \u003Cstrong\u003E Secretin\u003C/strong\u003E is produced by S cells in the duodenum to regulate pancreatic secretions.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Brunner glands secrete alkaline mucus containing bicarbonate to protect the duodenal mucosa from acidic chyme","Brunner glands are located in the submucosa of the duodenum"],"references":["Nightingale, J. M. (2012). Applied anatomy and physiology of the gastrointestinal tract (GIT). Gastrointestinal Tract Imaging E-Book: Gastrointestinal Tract Imaging E-Book, 45.","Podolsky, D. K., Camilleri, M., Fitz, J. G., Kalloo, A. N., Shanahan, F., \u0026 Wang, T. C. (Eds.). (2015). Yamada\u0027s textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49211"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15376"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data"